Reasoning: The paper deals with the performance analysis of a cognitive radio network with underlay spectrum sharing, which involves power allocation and cooperative diversity. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the impact of interference on the primary network, which is a system-level concern and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of relays and opportunistic relay selection involves communication protocols and techniques, which falls under the category of communication (cs.COMM). Finally, the paper considers the impact of fading channels, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
